---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Steelcase Gesture vs Leap Plus: Which Is Better for Tall People?",
    "url": "https://tallchairadvisor.com/gesture-vs-leap-plus",
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Tall Chair Advisor" }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://tallchairadvisor.com" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Best Office Chairs", "item": "https://tallchairadvisor.com/best-office-chairs" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Gesture vs Leap Plus", "item": "https://tallchairadvisor.com/gesture-vs-leap-plus" }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout
  title="Steelcase Gesture vs Leap Plus: Which Is Better for Tall People? | Tall Chair Advisor"
  description="Gesture vs Leap Plus compared on dimensions, adjustability, and suitability for tall users 6ft and above."
  schema={schema}
>
  <header class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20 bg-secondary/30">
    <div class="container-article text-center">
      <h1 class="text-balance animate-fade-in">Steelcase Gesture vs Leap Plus</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg md:text-xl text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl mx-auto animate-slide-up">
        Comparing Steelcase's two flagship options for tall users
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <article class="container-article py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="prose-tca">
      <section>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          The Steelcase Gesture and Steelcase Leap Plus are both premium ergonomic chairs, but they are designed to
          solve different problems for tall users. The Gesture emphasizes arm mobility and posture flexibility, while
          the Leap Plus focuses on size accommodation, deeper seat adjustment, and higher weight capacity.
        </p>
        <p>
          This comparison looks at real-world fit factors—seat dimensions, adjustability, support feel, and overall
          usability—to help tall users determine which chair better matches their body type and working style.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Dimensional Comparison</h2>
        <p>
          The Steelcase Gesture typically offers a seat height range of approximately 16 to 21 inches and is designed
          to support a wide variety of seated postures. Its seat depth adjustment works well for many tall users, but
          the overall platform remains closer to standard sizing with a strong emphasis on upper-body ergonomics and
          arm movement.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Steelcase Leap Plus is built for users who need more physical room and adjustment margin. It provides a
          wider seat, deeper seat depth adjustment—often cited up to roughly 19.75 inches—and a much higher weight
          capacity, commonly listed up to 500 lbs. This makes it a better fit when standard chair dimensions feel
          restrictive.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>For Tall Users</h2>
        <p>
          For tall users with larger frames or those who regularly feel constrained by standard office chairs, the
          Leap Plus is generally the safer choice. Its larger seat platform and deeper adjustability help support
          longer legs and reduce the "perched" feeling that can occur when seat depth is too shallow.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Gesture is often a strong option for tall users with more average builds who prioritize movement and
          flexibility. Its arm system is particularly well suited for device-heavy workflows, where arm positioning
          changes frequently throughout the day.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Verdict</h2>
        <p>
          Choose the <strong>Steelcase Leap Plus</strong> if you need maximum size accommodation, deeper seat support,
          and higher weight capacity for long-term comfort.
        </p>
        <p>
          Choose the <strong>Steelcase Gesture</strong> if you are tall with a more average build and value advanced
          arm mobility and dynamic sitting support.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Read Full Reviews</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/review/gesture" class="link-internal">Steelcase Gesture Review</a></li>
          <li><a href="/review/leap-plus" class="link-internal">Steelcase Leap Plus Review</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <div class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-border">
        <a href="/best-office-chairs" class="link-internal">← Back to Best Office Chairs for Tall People</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
